0year%2C%20and%20to%20increase%20its%20hiring%20plans%20by%201%2C000%20people%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20that%20same%20logic%2C%20Apple's%20Wednesday%20announcement%20means%20it%20is%20planning%20on%20spending%20another%20%2425%20billion%20a%20year%20above%20its%20earlier%20plans.%20(No%20word%2C%20yet%2C%20about%20any%20additional%20hiring%2C%20though%20Apple%20did%20say%20its%20work%20with%20Corning%20would%20increase%20the%20workforce%20there%20by%2050%25.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20that's%20definitely%20some%20additional%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220d093dfc-4dc4-44a4-b0e5-a6ffdc7ffc1e%5C%22%3EWill%20Apple%20make%20iPhones%20in%20the%20US%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDoes%20that%20mean%20Apple%20is%20going%20to%20start%20making%20iPhones%20in%20the%20US%2C%20as%20Trump%20has%20demanded%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo.%20As%20we've%20discussed%20before%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-china-tariff-supply-chain-book-patrick-mcgee-peter-kafka-2025-05%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecreating%20the%20supply%20chain%20Apple%20would%20need%20to%20make%20iPhones%20in%20the%20US%20seems%20close%20to%20impossible%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20certainly%20not%20something%20that%20Apple%20could%20pull%20off%20in%20a%20few%20years%20%E2%80%94%20if%20it%20even%20wanted%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20was%20asked%20that%20question%20directly%20at%20the%20press%20conference%2C%20and%20was%20ready%20for%20it.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20content%20in%20there%20from%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20argued%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20glass%20deal%20and%20other%20elements%20made%20at%20least%20in%20part%20in%20America.%20But%20as%20far%20as%20actually%20putting%20that%20stuff%20together%20%E2%80%94%20which%20requires%20a%20complicated%20supply%20chain%20Cook%20spent%20years%20and%20billions%20overseeing%3F%20%26quot%3BThat%20will%20be%20elsewhere%20for%20a%20while%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20getting%20to%20stand%20next%20to%20the%20CEO%20of%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20valuable%20companies%2C%20while%20that%20CEO%20says%20he's%20going%20to%20invest%20in%20America%2C%20is%20most%20definitely%20valuable%20to%20Trump%2C%20who%20was%20beaming%20throughout%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20as%20if%20any%20particular%20number%20means%20much%20to%20Trump%2C%20who%20recently%20announced%20he%20was%20going%20to%20reduce%20drug%20prices%20by%20%26quot%3B1%2C500%20percent%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcwashington.com%2Fnews%2Fnational-international%2Ftrump-drug-prices-claim-fact-check%2F3971116%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhich%20is%20definitely%20not%20possible%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20is%20also%20flexible%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20announcements%20about%20Trump-directed%20spending%20in%20America.%20Like%20when%20he%20stood%20next%20to%20Cook%20during%20his%20first%20term%20and%20announced%20that%20Apple%20had%20opened%20a%20new%20plant%20in%20Texas%20at%20his%20behest.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.texastribune.org%2F2019%2F11%2F20%2Fdonald-trump-austin-visit-apple%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlso%20not%20true%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20does%20Apple%20get%20in%20return%3F%20It%20would%20most%20obviously%20like%20permanent%20relief%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-trump-tariffs-impact-prices-stagflation-us-economy-slok-apollo-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrump's%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20far%2C%20Trump%20has%20granted%20Apple%20some%20immunity%20from%20some%20of%20his%20tariffs%20on%20foreign%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20all%20of%20them%2C%20which%20is%20why%20Apple%20has%20said%20it%20will%20have%20paid%20some%20%242%20billion%20in%20tariffs%20over%20its%20last%20two%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20and%20other%20tech%20companies%20are%20also%20hoping%20Trump%20will%20keep%20pushing%20on%20their%20beh