20is%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20%3Cem%3Emasala%20%3C%2Fem%3Eby%20Indian%20labourers%20%E2%80%94%20pointing%20to%20how%20its%20use%20should%20be%20moderated%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raghav%20notes.%20%E2%80%9CAn%20overuse%20can%20be%20toxic.%20It%20makes%20the%20structure%20non-breathable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20Tiny%20Farm%20Fort%2C%20the%20brothers%20decided%20to%20use%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F284927%2Fkerala-eco-friendly-sustainable-mud-house-stays-cool-cost-efficient-construction%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecob%20as%20the%20material%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20vetting%20its%20feasibility%2C%20they%20relied%20on%20an%20old%20English%20saying%3A%20A%20cob%20house%20which%20has%20a%20good%20boot%20(good%20foundation)%20and%20good%20hat%20(roof%20with%20large%20overhangs)%20will%20survive%20a%20hundred%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FfXNSUfyfnrY%3Fsi%3DzTeYiwb87_8-vqEQ%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%20end%2C%20the%20strategic%20location%20of%20the%20homestay%20proves%20a%20boon.%20%E2%80%9CTiny%20Farm%20Fort%20is%20perched%20on%20a%20hill%20and%20gets%20good%20sunlight.%20In%20cases%20of%20heavy%20rainfall%2C%20the%20water%20runs%20down%20the%20valley%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Raghav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20just%20its%20exterior%2C%20but%20even%20the%20interiors%20in%20the%20home%20are%20reflective%20of%20sustainable%20design.%20For%20this%2C%20the%20brothers%20credit%20the%20group%20that%20chipped%20in%20to%20help%20them%20build%20the%20homestay.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20weren%E2%80%99t%20artists%2C%20but%20cob%20is%20such%20a%20forgiving%20material%20to%20work%20with%20that%20the%20process%20almost%20becomes%20intuitive%2C%E2%80%